%h2 Questions
%p 
  A couple of weeks ago, I got an email from Nick Galvin, a Features Writer with the <a href="http://smh.com.au/">Sydney Morning Herald</a>, asking if I&rsquo;d be interested in answering some quick questions about what&rsquo;s hot on the web for a feature in their weekly technology supplement for the &ldquo;interested home user&rdquo;, Icon. I jumped at the chance and thanks must go to
  %span.vcard
    %a.url.fn{ :href => "http://johnfallsopp.com/", :rel => "met colleague friend" } John Allsopp
  recommending me.
%p The piece was published today and I finally got see who the other people were. I put <a href="http://flickr.com/photos/lachlanhardy/2772460555/">a scan on my Flickrstream</a> so you can read the full text at either <a href="http://flickr.com/photos/lachlanhardy/2772460555/sizes/l/">Large</a> or <a href="http://flickr.com/photos/lachlanhardy/2772460555/sizes/o/">Original (bloody large)</a>. Huge thanks must go to the legendary <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/sengster/">Seng Mah</a> for yet again allowing me to use <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/sengster/1142378196/">his photo of me from last August</a> as my publicly respectable face.
%p <strong>Update:</strong> Turns out the article did get published online, so it&rsquo;s much <a href="http://www.smh.com.au/news/technology/dopple-your-fun/2008/08/16/1218307304122.html?page=fullpage">easier to read there</a>.

