%h2 Answers
%p
  What I found most interesting is comparing my answers with those of
  %span.vcard
    %a.fn.nickname.url{ :href => "http://www.moltn.com/", :rel => "met" } Cheryl
  ,
  %span.vcard
    %a.fn.nickname.url{ :href => "http://www.alertbutnotalarmed.com/", :rel => "met" }Virginia
  ,
  %span.vcard
    %a.fn.nickname.url{ :href => "http://toolmantim.com/", :rel => "met friend colleague" }Tim
  and John. The differences are more telling than the similarities, I think. Cheryl&rsquo;s answers are consumer-focused, John talks about the big picture and Tim can&rsquo;t help but dish on what&rsquo;s important to developers. Of the four, Virginia&rsquo;s are probably closest to mine in ideas, although hers are expressed far more beautifully. (And she led me to <a href="http://penguinclassics.tumblr.com/">a gorgeous new theme</a> for my <a href="http://lachstock.tumblr.com/" rel="me">tumblelog</a>!)
%p I copped a bit of a ribbing at work about the reference in the standfirst to &lsquo;internet gurus&rsquo;. Fair enough. I find it amusing too. Thing is, though, that I know some other internet gurus.
%p Anybody willing to spend any time at all reading my infrequent posts is automatically qualified as pretty damn interested in the internet (or related to me. Hi, Mum!). So I want to know what you would have answered. What are your responses to the three questions? You don&rsquo;t have to stick to 180 words like we did!
%ol
  %li What are the three things online that are exciting you most?
  %li What gadget do you never leave home without? <em>And given most everybody will say their phone or their laptop, <strong>why?</strong></em>
  %li What will be the Next Big Thing?
